</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keokekin>Keoke Kin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 6:51:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=494.topic&index=116>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What happends to a fact inferred?</span><hr size=1> From I've deduced from what has been said, these four have been created.<br>
Who created them? And WHERE are these people?<br>
This is my proposal:<br>
They are created by a rogue band of scientists in an effort to combat these vampires. Of course, they had to keep their efforts discreet, or they would be shut down almost immediately, (nearly)irrelevent of how much proof they had. Let's face it; some nerds wasting money to combat a mythical race of blood-sucking, supernatural beings is hardly an incentive to provide said currency, and they had to fund the project somehow...<br>
The four are prototypes, each a different part of a big experiment to create a single being with all four powers.<br>
Unfortunately, before their final phase was completed (probably giving them training to use their power) the vampires infiltrated their base of operations. The vamps wanted that power, but before that happened, a single scientist activitated the four and self-destructed the lab. Before that, however, the vampires managed to kill almost every single person in the lab.<br>
Fast forward some indefinite length of time....(1 year)<br>
One of the scientists manage to bring the four together again. (Dr.Kain! &lt;-- Some random name), Each of the four have extremely scarce to non-existant knowledge of how to use their power. This is what Dr.Kain is for, he instructs them on their power's usage, and is generally the brains behind the brawn.<br>
Dr.Kain is NOT the head main, genious scientist, or the guy behind it all. Vampy's are a race thats lived for hundreds and thousands of years; they are _not_ that stupid. Those men would have died first. Dr Kain is more like the guy who polished the computers. He, himself, has only a little knowledge of what their powers really are.<br>
And so the hunt (more or less) begins.<br>
-=-=-=-<br>
I think that sounds a bit more like what our four heroes actually are, and give more depth to the story and plot.<br>
It also gives us the option of creating Super-Vamps; Vampy's with the same powers as our four heroes. I mean, _normal_ run-of-the-mill vampires are not going to be all that great of challenge to those four, especially as they learn more about their powers. Also, it gives us the option of (later in the story), adding a fifth hero; a person with all four powers. That person would be generally clue-less about his/her powers. He/She would also have to be a lot younger then the other four since he/she's was created after them.<br>
<br>
So, what do you think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neoangel>NeoAngel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/6/02 11:22:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=494.topic&index=117>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What happends to a fact inferred?</span><hr size=1> Keoke Kin, some good ideas but you're forgetting that it's not just those 4. There are 100 of them scattered all over the world. This would require some big money, which is why ('cos I'm writing the script, and working on the second part as we speak) I was going to have them made by an underground agency that controls some serious funding, like a crime syndicate or something. But there is no 5th child with all the powers because there are 25 of each element scattered all over the place. They were implanted in unsuspecting pregnant women when a &quot;routine ultrasound turned up something wrong and we had to operate, but don't worry, your baby is safe&quot;<br>
All 100 of the children are self-activating. At the age of 16, a chip in the back of their skull activates a host of dormant, self-replicating nanomachines in their blood flow which give them their power. Vampires didn't infiltrate and destroy the lab because there was no point, the children had already been spread around and so couldn't be tracked. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

